@startuml task-completion-protocol
' How an agentReported AgentTask's completion is admitted, recorded, and observed.
' Source of truth: docs/src/gateways/api/task-complete.md
!include _style.puml
' Notes here carry full sentences; give them room so they do not wrap ragged.
skinparam wrapWidth 400

participant "AgentTask\nReconciler" as R $ctrlBg
participant "apiserver" as K $mutedBg
participant "{taskName}-completion\nConfigMap" as CM $storeBg
participant "Gateway" as GW $gwBg
participant "Task Pod" as P $agentBg

== Provisioning (agentReported mode only) ==

R -> CM : Create, data: {}\nownerRef: AgentTask
R -> K : Create Role + RoleBinding\nverbs: update, patch\nresourceNames: {taskName}-completion

note over R, CM
  **No create verb.** RBAC resourceNames does not constrain
  create, so granting it would silently widen the gateway to
  every ConfigMap in the namespace. Pre-creating the mailbox
  here is what makes the name-scoping enforceable.
end note

R -> K : stamp status.currentPodUID = newPod.UID\n(once the Pod is observed via the informer)

== Completion ==

P -> GW : POST /v1/task/complete (mTLS)

GW -> GW : resolve source IP to Pod UID\nvia the Pod informer
alt informer-cache miss (new-Pod startup window)
  GW -> K : live List Pods in the cert-SAN namespace,\nfiltered by source IP
end

note over GW
  spec.artifacts, status.currentPodUID and status.phase
  are read from the gateway's existing AgentTask watch,
  so every gate below runs synchronously.
end note

alt no Pod resolved, even after the live fallback
  GW --> P : **401** unauthorized (retryable: false)
else calling Pod is not an AgentTask Pod
  GW --> P : **403** access_denied\nreason=NotAgentTaskPod (retryable: false)
else task has completion.condition: exitCode
  GW --> P : **403** access_denied\nreason=TaskNotAgentReported (retryable: false)
else UID != status.currentPodUID
  GW --> P : **403** access_denied\nreason=StalePodCompletion\n(retryable: **true**)
else status.phase already terminal
  GW --> P : **403** access_denied\nreason=TaskAlreadyCompleted (retryable: false)
else admitted

  GW -> GW : validate artifact names vs spec.artifacts\nsuccess: exact set | failure: no undeclared
  GW -> GW : validate sizes\n4 KiB per artifact | 32 KiB combined

  alt artifact-name rule violated
    GW --> P : **400** invalid_request (retryable: false)
  else size cap exceeded
    GW --> P : **413** request_too_large (retryable: false)
  else body valid
    GW -> CM : Patch payload\n(via the per-task scoped Role)
    alt Patch fails
      GW --> P : **503** internal_unavailable\n(retryable: true, Retry-After: 1)
    else patched
      GW --> P : **200** OK (empty body)
      CM -> R : ConfigMap watch fires
      R -> R : defensive artifact re-check\n(same per-status rule)
      R -> K : status.phase = Completing
    end
  end
end

note over R, P
  The informer fallback collapses new-Pod informer lag into the
  retryable **403 StalePodCompletion** path instead of leaking it
  as a terminal **401**. The reconciler stays the final authority
  on AgentTask state.
end note
@enduml
